    "client_msg_id": "41c54f92-ac29-4730-b660-b478c46571d6",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "*The Overedge Catalog: New Types of Research Organizations*\nby Samuel Arbesman\n<https://arbesman.net/overedge/>\n&gt; In cartography, most maps are bound by the straight lines at their borders. But occasionally, there are parts of the map that don’t quite fit. They bleed over the edge and yet still cry out for being included in a map. These are the _overedges_. The *Overedge Catalog* is devoted to collecting the intriguing new types of organizations and institutions that lie at *the intersection of the worlds of research and academia, non-profits, and tech startups*. This is a small but growing number of organizations, but hopefully by collecting and highlighting all of these here, it can spur further institutional innovation.",
